cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of energy-aware D2D LAN formation over cellular networks, which involves network optimization, game theory, and control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a game-theoretic framework to model the behavior of mobile users, which suggests the possibility of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Moreover, the paper proposes a punishment and incentive protocol to ensure cooperation among mobile users, which indicates the relevance of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also proposes an estimation algorithm to simulate the process of D2D LAN formation, which suggests the possibility of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework using simulation results, which suggests the relevance of cs.MM (Multimedia).
